<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<subsection component="1031">
  <title>Applications of the Derivative (<init>A</init>)</title>
  <assemblage xml:id="standard-calcI-A1">
    <title>Applications of the Derivative 1 (<init>A1</init>)</title>
    <p>
      I can use the first and second derivatives of a function to
      <ul>
	<li>
	  <p>find the critical numbers,</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	  <p>identify local extreme values,</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	  <p>identify the concavity of a function on an interval, and</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	  <p>identify inflection points.</p>
	</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </assemblage>
   
  <assemblage xml:id="standard-calcI-A2">
    <title>Applications of the Derivative 2 (<init>A2</init>)</title>
    <p>
      I can use the information from <xref ref="standard-calcI-F2" text="title"/> and <xref ref="standard-calcI-A1" text="title"/> to sketch the graph of a function.
    </p>
  </assemblage>

  <assemblage xml:id="standard-calcI-A3">
    <title>Applications of the Derivative 3 (<init>A3</init>)</title>
    <p>
      I can use the closed interval method to solve optimization problems.
    </p>
  </assemblage>
</subsection>
